  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "As I detailed it [here](https://ethereum.stackexchange.com/questions/15357/solidity-error-doc-tag-notice-not-valid-for-statements), having `///` in my code lead to solc giving me the following error: `Doc tag @notice not valid for statements`. I just wanted to comment with `//` but mistakenly added another `/`, which lead to the error.\r\nSince no line number was given, it took me a lot of time to detect the error.\r\n\r\nTo avoid it, I suggest that the Solidity compiler should be able to detect this error and return where it occurred (at least the line number).",
